wind. Using the HT method, we find\nthat the observed variations in $E_y$ are often in excellent agreement with the\nvariations in the magnetic field. The magnitude of $E_y$, however, is uncertain\ndue to the fact that the $L_\\text{eff}$ depends on the plasma environment. We\nderive an empirical model relating $L_\\text{eff}$ to the Debye length, which we\ncan use to improve the estimate of $E_y$ and consequently the estimated solar\nwind speed. The low frequency electric field provided by RPW is of high\nquality. Using deHoffmann-Teller analysis, Solar Orbiter's magnetic and\nelectric field measurements can be used to estimate the solar wind speed when\nplasma data is unavailable.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 8 Apr 2021 07:05:28 GMT"}],"update_date":"2021-12-15"}
